section.section:
Of the 6 master electrician members:
1 shall be from Baltimore City;
1 shall be from the area that consists of Caroline, Dorchester, Kent, Queen Anne's, Somerset, Talbot, Wicomico, and Worcester counties;
1 shall be from the area that consists of Baltimore, Cecil, and Harford counties;
1 shall be from the area that consists of Anne Arundel, Calvert, Charles, and St. Mary's counties;
1 shall be from the area that consists of Montgomery and Prince George's counties; and
1 shall be from the area that consists of Allegany, Carroll, Frederick, Garrett, Howard, and Washington counties.

text.section:
Each consumer member of the State Board:
shall be a member of the general public;
may not be a licensee or otherwise be subject to regulation by the State Board;
may not be required to meet the qualifications for the professional members of the State Board; and
may not, within 1 year before appointment, have had a financial interest in or have received compensation from a person regulated by the State Board.
